   <Ritual>
      <Quotations id="ritualQuotations">
         <ab>N28.44 (Kotwal and Kreyenbroek 2003: 102-3)</ab>
         <ab class="ab_indent"><em>pad </em> ẏeŋ́hē mē aṣ̌āt̰ hacā <em> jīw be baxšišn pad 3 bahr 2
               bahr ān ī zōhrag ud ēk ān ī barsom ay tāy ī *bastag kē az kust ī dašn-iš zōhrag
               pad-iš </em></ab>
         <ab class="ab_indent">At <em>ẏeŋ́hē mē aṣ̌āt̰ hacā</em> he has to divide the<em> jīw</em>
            in three parts. Two parts are for the <em>zōhrag</em> and one for the <em>barsom</em>,
            that is, for the tied twigs at whose right side is the <em>zōhrag</em>.</ab>
      </Quotations>
   </Ritual>
